This paper is about the evaluation of recommender systems, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sliding windows and monitoring the evolution of algorithms over time, which are concepts related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the importance of user feedback and the unpredictability of rates, which are topics related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
